# Hooks & Realtime

## Hook role

Hooks bridge UI ↔ stores ↔ services. Name: `use[Feature]` (e.g. `useMessages`, `useAuth`).

## Zustand selectors

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD — stable selector, no full-store destructure
const addMessage = useChatStore((s) => s.addMessage);
const messages = useChatStore((s) => s.messages[roomId] ?? EMPTY_MESSAGES);

// ❌ BAD
const store = useChatStore();
```

Use stable empty constants (`const EMPTY_MESSAGES: Message[] = []`) to avoid re-renders.

## Realtime subscriptions

Only in `src/hooks/`. Always cleanup:

```typescript
useEffect(() => {
  const channel = supabase
    .channel(`room:${roomId}`)
    .on("postgres_changes", { event: "INSERT", schema: "public", table: "messages", filter: `room_id=eq.${roomId}` },
      (payload) => addMessage(payload.new as Message))
    .subscribe();

  return () => { supabase.removeChannel(channel); };
}, [roomId, addMessage]);
```

Channel names: `room:${roomId}`, `global:messages`, `typing:${roomId}`.

## Optimistic updates (messages)

```typescript
const tempId = `temp-${Date.now()}`;
addOptimisticMessage(optimistic);
try {
  const sent = await messageService.sendMessage({ ... });
  replaceOptimisticMessage(tempId, sent);
} catch {
  removeMessage(tempId, roomId);
}
```

Use `useCallback` for handlers passed to list items.
